                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85077509 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117885" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3953-part1-item1">
                        <locus from="1v" to="60v">ff. 1v-60v</locus>
                        <note>
                           <p>Collection of letters written by the munshi or secretary Muhammad Faza'il Khan Bahadur for his masters Muhammad Ranmast Khan Bahadur and Asafjah Nizam 'Ali Khan Bahadur </p>
                           <p>Letters collected poshumously by the munshi's student (shāgird), Muhammad Ma'mur Khan, who organised them into 3 themed faṣl, with an initial preface and introduction </p>
                           <p>Introduction contains a useful discussion on iṣṭilāḥ or the usage of terminology </p>
                           <p>Dated colophon (f. 60v): ʿaṣr (mid afternoon), Wednesday, 11 Jum. II 1234/7 April 1819, at Arkāt (Arcot) </p>
                           <p>Pinkish tinted paper on folios 33-48 </p>
                           <p>Old nīm leaves preserved between folios to repel insects </p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                        <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21921">Inshā-'i Faz̤āʾil Khānī</title>
                        <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21921">انشاء فضائل خانى</title>
